1941;;Playmates;;American;;David Butler;;Kay Kyser, Lupe Velez;;musical comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Playmates_(1941_film);;Lulu Monahan, played by Patsy Kelly, is a press agent for John Barrymore, who plays himself. Lulu tries to get a sponsor for his radio program. Lulu and the agent for bandleader Kay Kyser, playing himself, make up a story that the great Shakespearean actor will teach Kyser how to play Shakespeare.[3]